@Hinsteny

@nickwongwong  hi, thanks for your contribution

If we modify the inital state of `ready` field, shall it can be adapted to the expose way by `ServiceConfig`?

`ServiceConfig` may not start `DubboStarter` and QOS `Ready` command will alaways fail.

Have a try at this:
`@Configuration
public class DubboConfig {

    @Reference
    private DemoServie demoService;

    @Bean
    public DemoServie demoServie() {
        return demoService;
    }   
}`

> Have a try at this:
> `@Configuration
> public class DubboConfig {
> 
> ```
> @Reference
> private DemoServie demoService;
> 
> @Bean
> public DemoServie demoServie() {
>     return demoService;
> }   
> ```
> 
> }`

Yes, I use the same as yours, and you can also use the following methods on 2.7.8
```
    @DubboReference(protocol = "dubbo", check = false, timeout = 5000, retries = 1)
    public DemoService setDemoService(DemoService demoService){
        return demoService;
    }
```

version 2.7.9 
package : org.apache.dubbo.config.spring.contex
DubboLifecycleComponentApplicationListener.java  line 54

    public DubboLifecycleComponentApplicationListener(ApplicationContext applicationContext) {
        super(applicationContext);
    }

这里个构造方法是有参数的， 那么就没有默认的无惨构造方法了，

在  2.7.8中没有上面的方法，所以有无参构造方法
临时解决办法 是在 DubboLifecycleComponentApplicationListener 加上无参构造方法

    public DubboLifecycleComponentApplicationListener( ) {

    }

